<subSubSection box="[197,1412,577,601]" pageId="4" pageNumber="23" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,504,1213]" box="[197,1412,577,601]" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,331,577,601]" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is dedicated to César Monzó, a colleague who collected this species for the first time.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="23" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,504,1213]" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,319,613,638]" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species belongs to the 
<taxonomicName box="[635,695,614,637]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Zodarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusio">
<emphasis box="[635,695,614,637]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">pusio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. It is very similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[1001,1091,614,637]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Zodarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusio">
<emphasis box="[1001,1091,614,637]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">Z. pusio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
both in colour and size. Males are distinguished by the shape of the terminal part of the tibial apophysis. Females are distinguished by the presence of a roof-like structure in the median plate of epigyne.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="23" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,504,1213]" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,342,721,746]" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">Description.</emphasis>
Male. Total length 1.7–2.3 mm; prosoma 0.9–1.1 long, 0.7–0.8 wide. Colour: Coxae pale, carapace yellow, legs segments yellow, sternum pale, abdomen dorsally brown, ventrally pale, dark spot around eyes, sternum with thin brown margin. Palp. Tibial apophysis with ventro-lateral lobe at base, bent but not hooked terminally, on the retrolateral side with a tiny pointed terminal apophysis (
<figureCitation box="[926,995,829,853]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 6. Z" captionStartId="4.[151,263,1883,1906]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,1279,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,1269,1862]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 6. Z. cesari. 3. Male palp, ventral view. 4. Male palp, lateral view. 5. Epigyne, ventral view. 6. Vulva, dorsal view. Scales: 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277159/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[979,995,829,853]" pageId="4" pageNumber="23" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Distal part of median apophysis slen- der, elongated and pointed (
<figureCitation box="[462,531,865,889]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 6. Z" captionStartId="4.[151,263,1883,1906]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,1279,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,1269,1862]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 6. Z. cesari. 3. Male palp, ventral view. 4. Male palp, lateral view. 5. Epigyne, ventral view. 6. Vulva, dorsal view. Scales: 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277159/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[514,531,865,889]" pageId="4" pageNumber="23" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Embolus rather straight and S-shaped.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,504,1213]" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">
Female. Total length 2.3–2.8 mm; prosoma 
<number box="[685,694,901,925]" pageId="4" pageNumber="23" value="1.0">1</number>
–1.2 long, 0.7–0.9 wide. Colour as in male. Epigyne. Paired openings surrounded anterio-laterally by sclerotised rims converging in the centre and forming a roof-like structure in the centre of the plate (
<figureCitation box="[422,493,973,997]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 6. Z" captionStartId="4.[151,263,1883,1906]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,1279,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,1269,1862]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 6. Z. cesari. 3. Male palp, ventral view. 4. Male palp, lateral view. 5. Epigyne, ventral view. 6. Vulva, dorsal view. Scales: 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277159/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[477,493,973,997]" pageId="4" pageNumber="23" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
). Vulva with rounded receptacula separated by 2.5x their diameter, ducts short Sshaped (
<figureCitation box="[244,312,1009,1033]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 6. Z" captionStartId="4.[151,263,1883,1906]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,1279,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,1269,1862]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 6. Z. cesari. 3. Male palp, ventral view. 4. Male palp, lateral view. 5. Epigyne, ventral view. 6. Vulva, dorsal view. Scales: 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277159/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[296,312,1009,1033]" pageId="4" pageNumber="23" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
